-- State Construction Said to Receive $386 Million Eight-Bank Syndicated Loan
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-24T02:44:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/state-construction-said-to-receive-386-million-eight-bank-syndicated-loan.html

          
          
             China State Construction
International Holdings Ltd. , which provides civil engineering
services in Hong Kong, signed a HK$3 billion ($386 million)
five-year loan to boost business development.  
 The eight lenders were Bank of China (Hong Kong),
Agricultural Bank of China, Bank of Communications Co., Bank of
East Asia Ltd., BNP Paribas SA, HSBC Holdings Plc, Standard
Chartered Plc and Wing Lung Bank, the company said in a
statement posted on its website.  
 The loanâ€™s final size was increased from HK$1.5 billion,
the company said. China State Construction started its
construction business in Hong Kong in 1979, according to its
website.  
